description:
As an admin user
  I want to manage the dashboard and categories
  So that I can view summary information and perform CRUD operations on categories

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_007 - Verify search functionality when an incorrect category name is entered

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin logs in with valid credentials
the admin navigates to the Categories page
the admin clicks on the search input field
the admin enters an incorrect category name "XYZ123NonExistent"
the admin clicks the Search button
the system should not return any matching categories
a user friendly message should be displayed such as "No results found"
the system should not crash or show incorrect results

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_008 - Verify whether the Admin dashboard is loaded after successful login

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin enters correct username and password
the admin clicks on the Login button
the system should navigate to the Dashboard
the Dashboard elements should be visible without any error message

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_009 - Verify whether the Admin Dashboard navigation menu is highlighted correctly

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin logs in with valid credentials
the navigation menu should be visible on the dashboard
the admin clicks on the Categories menu item
the Categories menu should be highlighted

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_010 - Verify the display of Category, Plants, and Sales Summary information on the Admin Dashboard

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin logs in with valid credentials
the admin navigates to the Dashboard
the dashboard should display category summary information
the dashboard should display plants summary information
the dashboard should display sales summary information
the displayed values should be accurate without UI errors

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_011 - Verify whether the Add category button is visible on the admin category page

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin logs in with valid credentials
the admin navigates to the Categories page
the Add Category button should be clearly visible
the Add Category button should be enabled and properly aligned

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_012 - Verify the functionality of the Cancel button on the Add category page

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin logs in with valid credentials
the admin navigates to the Categories page
the admin clicks on the Add Category button
the admin clicks on the Cancel button
the system should cancel the operation
the admin should be redirected to the category page
no new category should be added

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_013 - Verify that the category name field does not accept fewer than 3 characters

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin logs in with valid credentials
the admin navigates to the Categories page
the admin clicks on the Add Category button
the admin enters a category name with less than 3 characters "ab"
the admin clicks the Save button
the system should not accept the category name
a validation error message should be displayed
the category should not be saved

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_015 - Verify whether the category name field does not accept more than 10 characters

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin logs in with valid credentials
the admin navigates to the Categories page
the admin clicks on the Add Category button
the admin enters a category name with more than 10 characters "Abcdefghijk"
the admin clicks the Save button
the system should not accept the category name
a validation error message should be displayed
the category should not be saved

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_ADMIN_016 - Verify whether the edit and delete actions are enabled on the category page

steps.name: the admin is on the login page
the admin logs in with valid credentials
the admin navigates to the Categories page
at least one category should exist in the system
the Edit action should be visible and enabled for each category
the Delete action should be visible and enabled for each category
the admin can initiate Edit or Delete actions without errors

name: Dashboard and Category Module - Admin Tests

description:
As a regular user
  I want to view and navigate categories
  So that I can browse category information with pagination and filtering

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_USER_001 - Verify the functionality whether the list of categories are loading with the pagination

steps.name: the user is logged in to the system as User
the user navigates to the Categories page
the categories should be displayed on the page
the pagination controls should be visible including Next and Previous buttons
the user clicks on the Next button or page number 2
the categories should be loaded and should not repeat from the first page
the user clicks on the Previous button
the first page of categories should be loaded
navigating through each page should load categories correctly

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_USER_003 - Verify the functionality of filtering by parent category

steps.name: the user is logged in to the system as User
the user navigates to the Categories page
the parent category filter dropdown should be visible
the user clicks the parent category dropdown
the user selects a parent category from the dropdown
the category list should display only categories related to the selected parent
no non-matching categories should be displayed
the user resets or clears the filter
all categories should be displayed

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_USER_004 - Verify the functionality of sorting by ID

steps.name: the user is logged in to the system as User
the user navigates to the Categories page
the ID column should be visible and clickable
the user clicks on the ID column header
the categories should be sorted in ascending order of ID
the user clicks on the ID column header again
the categories should be sorted in descending order of ID
the user resets the page
the default order should be restored

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_USER_005 - Verify the functionality of sorting by Name

steps.name: the user is logged in to the system as User
the user navigates to the Categories page
the Name column should be visible and clickable
the user clicks on the Name column header
the categories should be sorted in ascending alphabetical order
the user clicks on the Name column header again
the categories should be sorted in descending alphabetical order
the user resets the page
the default order should be restored

elements.name: TC_DASHBOARD_UI_USER_006 - Verify the functionality of sorting by Parent category

steps.name: the user is logged in to the system as User
the user navigates to the Categories page
the Parent column should be visible and clickable
the user clicks on the Parent column header
the categories should be sorted by parent category
the user clicks on the Parent column header again
the categories should be sorted in reverse order by parent category
the user resets the page
the default order should be restored

name: Category Module - User Tests
